
[1]residuary

   RESID'UARY, a. [L. residuus. See Reside.]

   Pertaining to the residue or part remaining; as the residuary advantage
   of an estate.

   Residuary legatee, in law, the legatee to whom is bequeathed the part
   of goods and estate which remains after deducting all the debts and
   specific legacies.
